# PART 1: Create Firebase Project (2 minutes)

## Step 1.1: Go to Firebase Console
1. Open your web browser
2. Go to: **https://console.firebase.google.com**
3. Sign in with your Google account (the one you want to own this project)

## Step 1.2: Create New Project
1. Click the **"Add project"** button (or **"Create a project"** if this is your first one)
   
   ![Add project button - large purple/blue button at the center]

## Step 1.3: Enter Project Details
1. **Project name**: Enter your school name
   - Example: "Little Star High School" or "Green Valley Academy"
   - Firebase will auto-generate a Project ID below the name
   
2. **Note your Project ID**: 
   - You'll see something like: `little-star-high-school-abc123`
   - **WRITE THIS DOWN** - you'll need it later!
   - This is what you'll enter in our app

3. Click **"Continue"**

## Step 1.4: Google Analytics (Optional)
1. You'll see "Enable Google Analytics for this project?"
2. **Recommended**: Toggle it **OFF** (you can enable later if needed)
3. Click **"Create project"**

## Step 1.5: Wait for Creation
1. Firebase will create your project (takes 10-30 seconds)
2. You'll see a progress bar
3. When done, click **"Continue"**

**‚úÖ Part 1 Complete!** You now have a Firebase project.

