# PART 2: Set Up Billing Account (2 minutes)

## ‚ö†Ô∏è Why Billing is Required:
- Firebase needs a billing account for programmatic access (API usage)
- **You get a FREE tier** worth $10-25/month
- You WON'T be charged unless you exceed free limits
- Small schools typically stay within free tier = **$0/month cost**

## Step 2.1: Link Billing Account
1. In Firebase Console, you might see a banner saying "Upgrade to Blaze plan"
   - OR go to: **‚öôÔ∏è Project Settings** (bottom left) ‚Üí **Usage and billing** tab
   
2. Click **"Modify plan"** or **"Upgrade project"**

3. Select **"Blaze (Pay as you go)"** plan
   - Don't worry - this includes the FREE tier!
   - Click **"Continue"**

## Step 2.2: Create Billing Account (First Time Only)
**If you already have a billing account**: Skip to Step 2.3

**If this is your first time**:
1. Click **"Create billing account"**
2. Select your **Country**
3. Accept **Terms of Service** (check the box)
4. Click **"Continue"**

## Step 2.3: Add Payment Method
1. Enter your **Card details**:
   - Card number
   - Expiration date
   - CVV code
   - Cardholder name
   
2. Enter your **Billing address**

3. Click **"Start my free trial"** or **"Submit"**

## Step 2.4: Set Budget Alert (HIGHLY RECOMMENDED)
**Protect yourself from unexpected charges:**

1. Go to: **https://console.cloud.google.com/billing**

2. Select your billing account

3. Click **"Budgets & alerts"** (left menu)

4. Click **"Create Budget"**

5. Set up alert:
   - **Budget name**: "School App Alert"
   - **Projects**: Select your school project
   - **Budget type**: Specified amount
   - **Target amount**: $5 (or $10)
   - **Threshold rules**: 50%, 90%, 100%
   - Enter your email for alerts

6. Click **"Finish"**

**‚úÖ Part 2 Complete!** Billing is set up with protection.

