# PART 3: Enable Firebase Services (1 minute)

Now back in Firebase Console, enable the services your school app needs:

## Step 3.1: Enable Firestore Database
1. In Firebase Console, click **"Firestore Database"** (left menu)
2. Click **"Create database"**
3. Choose **"Start in production mode"**
4. Select **Region**: Choose closest to your location
   - Asia: `asia-south1` (Mumbai) or `asia-southeast1` (Singapore)
   - US: `us-central1`
   - Europe: `europe-west1`
5. Click **"Enable"**
6. Wait 10-20 seconds for creation

**‚úÖ Firestore enabled!**

## Step 3.2: Enable Authentication
1. Click **"Authentication"** (left menu)
2. Click **"Get started"**
3. Go to **"Sign-in method"** tab
4. Click on **"Email/Password"**
5. Toggle **"Enable"** to ON
6. Click **"Save"**

**‚úÖ Authentication enabled!**

## Step 3.3: Enable Storage
1. Click **"Storage"** (left menu)
2. Click **"Get started"**
3. Click **"Next"** (use default security rules)
4. Select same **Region** as Firestore
5. Click **"Done"**

**‚úÖ Storage enabled!**

## Step 3.4: Enable Cloud Messaging (FCM)
1. Click **"Cloud Messaging"** (left menu)
2. Click **"Get started"**
3. That's it! FCM is automatically enabled.

**‚úÖ Cloud Messaging enabled!**

