# PART 4: Register Your Web App (1 minute)

## Step 4.1: Go to Project Settings
1. Click the **‚öôÔ∏è gear icon** (top left, next to "Project Overview")
2. Select **"Project settings"**

## Step 4.2: Register Web App
1. Scroll down to **"Your apps"** section
2. Click the **Web icon** `</>`  (looks like: **</>**)
3. Enter **App nickname**: "School Web App"
4. **DO NOT** check "Also set up Firebase Hosting"
5. Click **"Register app"**
6. You'll see code snippet - **IGNORE IT** (we'll fetch this automatically)
7. Click **"Continue to console"**

**‚úÖ Web app registered!**

## Step 4.3: (Optional) Register Android App
**Only if you're using Android:**
1. In same "Your apps" section, click **Android icon** (Android robot)
2. Enter **Android package name**: 
   - Find this in your app's `android/app/build.gradle`
   - Look for `applicationId` (e.g., `com.yourschool.app`)
3. Enter **App nickname**: "School Android App"
4. Click **"Register app"**
5. Skip downloading `google-services.json` - we'll fetch automatically
6. Click **"Next"** ‚Üí **"Next"** ‚Üí **"Continue to console"**

## Step 4.4: (Optional) Register iOS App
**Only if you're using iOS:**
1. In same "Your apps" section, click **iOS icon** (Apple logo)
2. Enter **iOS bundle ID**: 
   - Find this in your app's `ios/Runner.xcodeproj/project.pbxproj`
   - Look for `PRODUCT_BUNDLE_IDENTIFIER`
3. Enter **App nickname**: "School iOS App"
4. Click **"Register app"**
5. Skip downloading `GoogleService-Info.plist` - we'll fetch automatically
6. Click **"Next"** ‚Üí **"Next"** ‚Üí **"Continue to console"**

**‚úÖ Apps registered!

